         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/10/76 ¶  ¶ By the Steamship "Durham", dear Dr Hooker, a Gentleman takes a case with living plants to London. ¶  In this are included for Kew 2 plants of Correa Lawrenciana, the var. with  ¶ crimson ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.10.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 187.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotations: 'J. S' [i.e. John Smith, Curator];<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>and: 'And Jay 11/77'. See J. Hooker to M, 11 January 1877 (in this edition as 77-01-11a).</p>
               </note>4/10/76</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By the Steamship "Durham", dear Dr Hooker, a Gentleman takes a case with living plants to London.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The first sentence is marked in the margin with a double line</seg>. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See J. Hooker to M, 11 January 1877<seg style="color: #000000; ">. The Kew Inwards Book, 1873-77, p. 422, entry 16, dated 9 January 1877 identifies the passenger as 'Wm Bull', but he has not been further identified.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> In this are included for Kew 2 plants of <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>, the var. with <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">crimson</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">flowers</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wished your father could have lived to see this glorious plant of his<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">William Hooker named the species in W. Hooker (1834-42), vol. 1, p. 254.</p>
               </note> in cultivation. You know of course that C. Lawrenciana is almost subalpine, and that it ought to stand on sheltered places the English lowland-winter, if sightly<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">slightly?</p>
               </note> protected. It only commences to grow in altitudes where C. speciosa ceases to grow.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It becomes a small tree in forest vallies, and the foliage with its dark green lustre is magnificent, while the flowers of this variety, as yet only known from my place of discovery,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Between Apollo Bay and Cape Otway, Vic.; see M to R. Gunn, 12 June 1867.</p>
               </note> are as magnificent as that of the scarlet variety of C. speciosa.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Correa%20speciosa">Correa speciosa</name>
            </p>
